426] Losartan''s prevention of angiotensin II binding causes vascular smooth muscle relaxation, lowering blood pressure.[L7423,L7426]



Angiotensin II would otherwise bind to the AT<sub>1</sub> receptor and induce vasoconstriction, raising blood pressure.[L7423,L7426]', 'Losartan is an angiotensin II receptor blocker used to treat hypertension, diabetic nephropathy, and to reduce the risk of stroke.[A1033,L7423,L7426] Losartan has a long duration of action as it is given once daily.[L7423,L7426] Patients taking losartan should be regularly monitored for hypotension, renal function, and potassium levels.[L7423,L7426]', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
